WEBVTT

00:02.833 --> 00:04.000
- VERNON: Previously
on "Still the King"--

00:04.100 --> 00:05.867
- Crop circles are known
to emit high levels of--

00:05.967 --> 00:07.067
- BOTH: --electromagnetic
radiation.

00:07.167 --> 00:08.567
- I have a group of my own.

00:08.667 --> 00:10.200
We are currently accepting
members of all genders.

00:10.300 --> 00:12.700
- You can't invite my girlfriend
to join your dumb group.

00:12.800 --> 00:14.333
- He just did.
- You watch yourself.

00:14.433 --> 00:16.133
- I'm trying to do
the right thing by you.

00:16.233 --> 00:17.533
I made this whole mess.

00:17.633 --> 00:19.767
My career, missing out
on my little girl growing up.

00:19.867 --> 00:22.700
Now, I just wanna get back
to the real me, my music.

00:22.800 --> 00:24.367
- Well, you potential fathers
need to start

00:24.467 --> 00:25.967
contributing to the household.

00:26.067 --> 00:27.067
- I got a job.

00:27.167 --> 00:28.833
- I'm king stallion
around these parts.

00:28.933 --> 00:30.700
- Well, maybe there's
a new deputy in town.

00:34.100 --> 00:39.200
- [chanting] UTI, UTI, UTI.

00:39.300 --> 00:41.433
- WALT: Hear ye, hear ye,

00:41.533 --> 00:44.167
we are here in recognition
of the undiscovered.

00:44.267 --> 00:46.200
Let no person be here

00:46.300 --> 00:48.533
unless they're here
of their own free will.

00:48.633 --> 00:53.567
Do you, Leia Fityous,
vow to seek out the unknown?

00:53.667 --> 00:54.633
- I do.

00:54.733 --> 00:58.133
- And if the unknown
becomes the known,

00:58.233 --> 00:59.467
do you vow to seek out

00:59.567 --> 01:03.067
an entirely different
and unrelated, unknown thing?

01:03.167 --> 01:04.200
- Sure.

01:04.300 --> 01:06.433
- Well then,
I hereby welcome you

01:06.533 --> 01:10.967
to the brotherhood of
the--sisterhood.

01:11.067 --> 01:12.100
- Sibling--sibling hood.

01:12.200 --> 01:13.633
- Sibling hood?

01:13.733 --> 01:15.667
Moving on.

01:15.767 --> 01:17.467
I, Walter Baines Murray,

01:17.567 --> 01:20.600
hereby welcome you
to the founding chapter

01:20.700 --> 01:22.900
of Ultra Terrestrial
Investigations,

01:23.067 --> 01:27.067
henceforth knowns as UTI--

01:27.100 --> 01:28.800
- What?

01:30.567 --> 01:33.067
- Damn it, Terry.
- Come on, man.

01:33.100 --> 01:36.133
- Cool if I eat my bologna sando
in here?

01:36.233 --> 01:38.367
- I gotta go.
I should get back to work.

01:38.467 --> 01:42.533
- *

01:46.200 --> 01:47.600
- Enjoy that sandwich.

01:47.700 --> 01:51.700
- *

01:57.500 --> 02:01.433
- [smoke detector sounds]

02:02.633 --> 02:04.767
- * Still the King *

02:07.967 --> 02:11.400
- So, Ronnie, is there anything
you wanna say to me today?

02:11.500 --> 02:16.233
- Um...you look beautiful.

02:16.333 --> 02:17.667
- Thank you.

02:17.767 --> 02:21.067
But is there anything more
today specific you wanna say?

02:21.167 --> 02:23.700
- You look beautiful today.

02:26.167 --> 02:27.200
- Whoo!

02:27.300 --> 02:29.067
It's a really special day.

02:29.133 --> 02:31.467
- Oh, thank you.

02:31.567 --> 02:35.500
- I was lying in bed last night
and had an epiphany.

02:35.600 --> 02:38.267
- Oh my God, you better
wash your sheets, Vernon.

02:38.367 --> 02:40.500
- Ever since I got
my old song book back,

02:40.600 --> 02:42.567
it's like the lights came on.

02:42.667 --> 02:45.133
I need to go somewhere
and play my music for people

02:45.233 --> 02:46.933
that care about the songs.

02:47.067 --> 02:51.067
- Is there anything about me
today that you wanna say?

02:51.167 --> 02:53.833
- You...look beautiful.

02:57.100 --> 02:58.567
- Morning.
- Morning.

02:58.667 --> 03:01.367
- Um, I am headed
off to school.

03:01.467 --> 03:02.600
I love you.

03:02.700 --> 03:04.667
- And?

03:04.767 --> 03:07.067
- I respect you as a person.

03:07.167 --> 03:08.267
Bye, Dad.

03:08.367 --> 03:10.300
- Stay out of trouble.
- You, too.

03:10.400 --> 03:11.733
Nope.

03:11.833 --> 03:13.533
- Well, anyway,
I better hit the bricks, too.

03:13.633 --> 03:15.067
Gotta strike
while the iron's hot.

03:15.100 --> 03:16.300
You know what I'm saying?

03:16.400 --> 03:18.133
- Oh yeah, my iron's
pretty hot, too, you know?

03:18.233 --> 03:20.333
Uh, probably so hot
it'd burn my shirt right off me

03:20.433 --> 03:21.667
before it even got
the wrinkles out.

03:21.767 --> 03:23.800
- It's the wrong
kind of iron, dumbass.

03:23.900 --> 03:24.967
- Oh thank you, sir.

03:25.067 --> 03:26.567
- I wasn't getting that for you.

03:29.600 --> 03:31.400
- I can't believe it.

03:31.500 --> 03:34.067
They forgot my [bleep] birthday.

03:34.133 --> 03:35.767
- *

03:35.867 --> 03:36.833
- Hey, hey.

03:36.933 --> 03:38.800
Whoo, listen up.

03:38.900 --> 03:41.333
I bet you all are wondering
why I called you here today.

03:41.433 --> 03:42.833
- To pay us
for last week's gig?

03:42.933 --> 03:44.167
- Nope.

03:44.267 --> 03:46.900
This band has been playing
like a motorcycle orchestra

03:47.067 --> 03:50.533
with a ZZ Top backbone
and Springsteen attitude.

03:50.633 --> 03:51.933
- He's right.
We've been kicking ass.

03:52.067 --> 03:54.833
- But what good is it
if the songs kick ass

03:54.933 --> 03:58.100
